Chester Open Book,

On nudity from the lecturers point of view, even though instructors have a long history of nudity, I am afraid it is besieged by political correctness and health and safety antagonism. Lecturers have been petitioned to stop jogging on campus naked, taking a naked walk to the car park at lunchtime and other things too numerous to mention. I sense there is a possible conflict between what lecturer Adam does and what is seen to be appropriate by the majority of mature undergraduates.

Possibly it is possible that the Health and Safety bulls might eye up Adam in future. At present he can easily get away with it because he is doing something modest by comparison with a bikini. I am sure the very same bull’s would have first denied his right to run nude years ago. Imagine a proffered sit down with the Health and Safety CEO, the Chief of Staff, the Domestic Bursar and the Head of HR …
